Package org.logevents.impl

Interface LogEventGenerator

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ConditionalLogEventGenerator
    public interface LogEventGenerator
    Internal interface that is used by all calls to Logger.error(java.lang.String), Logger.warn(java.lang.String), Logger.info(java.lang.String), Logger.debug(java.lang.String) and Logger.trace(java.lang.String). There are three implementations: NullLoggingEventGenerator is used for all log events that are below the logger threshold, LevelLoggingEventGenerator is used for all log events that are to be logged and ConditionalLogEventGenerator
